AIM: 
To write a C program to sort a list of elements in ascending order using the Insertion Sort 
technique. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Read the number of elements n. 
3. Read n elements into the array arr[]. 
4. For i = 1 to n-1: 
 ->Set key = arr[i], j = i-1. 
 ->While j >= 0 and arr[j] > key: 
a. Move arr[j] to arr[j+1], decrement j. 
 Place key in arr[j+1]. 
5. Display the sorted array. 
6. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
int main() { 
int arr[50], n, i, j, key; 
printf("Enter number of elements: "); 
scanf("%d", &n); 
printf("Enter %d elements:\n", n); 
for (i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
scanf("%d", &arr[i]); 
} 
// Insertion Sort 
for (i = 1; i < n; i++) { 
key = arr[i]; 
j = i - 1; 
while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) { 
arr[j + 1] = arr[j]; 
j--; 
} 
arr[j + 1] = key; 
} 
printf("Sorted array (Ascending Order):\n"); 
for (i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
printf("%d ", arr[i]); 
} 
printf("\n"); 
return 0; 
} 
 
 
